value: Breeds from the north coast of the Chukchi Peninsula and Cape Lis- burne, Alaska, south on both sides of Bering Sea (and islands therein) and the North Pacific Ocean to the Kurile Islands (perhaps also Hokkaido) on the west and to the Santa Barbara Islands on the east. Chiefly resident, a few wintering south to northern Lower California.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Primarily pelagic; nests on islands and coastal slopes in ground burrows, sometimes under boulders and piles of rocks, occasionally under dense vegetation.
